<TITLE> Govt to rehabilitate 'innocents' caught up in miltancy </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Apr 21 (bdnews24.com) - The government is moving to rehabilitate "innocents" who have been drawn misguidedly into militancy, the state minister for home said Tuesday. "Some unfortunate people have become involved in militancy by being led astray," Tanjim Ahmed said Tuesday. Militants recruited 'freshers' at three levels, he said. The first being innocent students or youths, the second tier being those with organisational experience and the third level comprising those who could be trained to infiltrate into army and various administrative branches, said Tanjim. Home minister Sahara Khatun and the state minister were conversing with newly elected representatives of the Crime Reporters Association of Bangladesh at the secretariat The home minister said, "Many militants have confessed under section-164 'Sheikh Hasina was the key target. Every effort would be made to kill her'." She said, "A ring has been active since we came to power." She called on journalists present for constructive criticism that would help the government. "We welcome any constructive criticism. You can give us advice to take the country on the path of progress." The country's first female home minister apprised CRAB leaders of her government's various steps in its first hundred days. b
